{"id": 19061, "date": "1988-08-26T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1988-08-26T18:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=19061"}, "modified": "2026-02-23T21:12:18", "modified_gmt": "2026-02-24T05:12:18", "slug": "matr-bruce-springsteen-and-mike-ness-bad-luck", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1988/08/26/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-mike-ness-bad-luck/", "title": {"rendered": "Bad Luck"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>If you were with me about six months ago, you may remember our spotlight on Bruce&#8217;s studio guest appearance with Mike Ness on &#8220;Misery Loves Company.&#8221;</p>\n<p>I led that article stating that Bruce had been a fan of Social Distortion (Ness&#8217; band) since the early nineties. It&#8217;s a pretty safe bet that one of the songs that originally grabbed his attention was &#8220;Bad Luck.&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/tQOJY4NXYzM?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8220;Bad Luck&#8221; was the lead single for\u00a0<em>Somewhere Between Heaven and Hell</em>, Social Distortion&#8217;s fourth studio album in 1992. It quickly became&#8211;and remains&#8211;the band&#8217;s biggest hit, peaking at #2 on the Billboard Modern Rock Tracks (now known as Alternative Airplay) chart.</p>\n<p>Years later, Ness made two appearances with Bruce Springsteen and the E Street Band, once on the Working on a Dream Tour and again on the Wrecking Ball Tour. On both occasions, the song they played together was Social Distortion&#8217;s biggest hit.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/NCHI_PBXRvk?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Six years after Ness&#8217; last E Street stage appearance, Bruce returned the favor when Social Distortion played Asbury Park&#8217;s Sea.Hear.Now. Festival in the autumn of 2018. Bruce took a rare rocking break from his Broadway schedule to join the band for three songs that night: the aforementioned &#8220;Misery Loves Company,&#8221; a terrific cover of &#8220;Ring of Fire,&#8221; and (of course) &#8220;Bad Luck.&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/imPrGD5RIT8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>Bad Luck<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> April 16, 2009 (Los Angeles, CA)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> September 30, 2018 (Asbury Park, NJ)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 June 25, 2020</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>An avid Social Distortion fan, Bruce was bound to cover their biggest hit. Watch Bruce team up&#8211;three times&#8211;with Mike Ness and Social Distortion on &#8220;Bad Luck.&#8221; </p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 67985, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}}, "categories": [4, 3612, 5], "tags": [709, 708, 2412], "class_list": ["post-19061", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "category-great", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-bad-luck", "tag-mike-ness", "tag-social-distortion"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/admin-ajax-33.jpg?fit=1198%2C1182&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-4Xr", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 15115, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1988/03/01/matr-mike-ness-and-bruce-springsteen-misery-loves-company/", "url_meta": {"origin": 19061, "position": 0}, "title": "Misery Loves Company", "author": "Ken", "date": "March 1, 1988", "format": false, "excerpt": "Mike Ness has played with Bruce on stage on several occasions, but they only collaborated in the studio once. Listen to their \"Misery Loves Company\" inside.", "rel": 